for? I don't want to talk to you.

500
01:09:56,960 --> 01:09:59,190
Pentangeli's set up a meeting
with the Rosato brothers.

501
01:09:59,296 --> 01:10:01,628
- He's gonna go for their deal.
- Oh, God.

502
01:10:01,732 --> 01:10:04,257
- Will he come alone?
- I don't know anything.

503
01:10:04,368 --> 01:10:06,928
- You got me in deep enough already.
- Just go along.

504
01:10:07,037 --> 01:10:09,028
Everything will be allright, Fredo.

505
01:10:09,139 --> 01:10:11,437
Pentangeli says he's
willing to make a deal.

506
01:10:11,542 --> 01:10:14,443
All we wanna know is
if he's on the level.

507
01:10:16,046 --> 01:10:19,072
You guys lied to me. I don't
want you to call me anymore.

508
01:10:19,183 --> 01:10:21,651
Your brother's not
gonna find out we talked.

509
01:10:21,752 --> 01:10:24,653
I don't know what you're talkin' about.

510
01:10:34,631 --> 01:10:36,531
Who was that?

511
01:10:36,633 --> 01:10:38,533
Uh, wrong number.

512
01:10:45,743 --> 01:10:48,644
Frank, I got nobody here.

513
01:10:48,746 --> 01:10:50,646
- Wait in the car,
Cheech. - Frankie--

514
01:10:50,748 --> 01:10:52,648
It's okay, Cheech.

515
01:10:59,790 --> 01:11:03,191
- What's this, Rosato?
- A lucky "C" note for our new deal.

516
01:11:06,630 --> 01:11:09,030
Richie. Give us a taste, huh?

517
01:11:13,704 --> 01:11:17,663
Yeah, we're all real happy
about your decision, Frankie.

518
01:11:17,775 --> 01:11:22,212
- You're not gonna regret it.
- I don't like this "C" note.

519
01:11:22,312 --> 01:11:24,780
I take that as an insult.

520
01:11:24,882 --> 01:11:27,112
Michael Corleone says hello.

521
01:11:44,201 --> 01:11:47,295
Get him in! Close the fuckin' door!

522
01:11:47,404 --> 01:11:49,804
Your friend the
cop. What the--

523
01:11:49,907 --> 01:11:52,637
Hey, Rich, it's dark in here.

524
01:11:52,743 --> 01:11:57,146
- Are you open or closed?
- I just come in to clean up.

525
01:12:00,517 --> 01:12:02,849
What's the matter?

526
01:12:02,953 --> 01:12:05,922
- Is that somethin' on the floor?
- Carmine, no, no. Not here!

527
01:12:06,023 --> 01:12:08,491
- Not here!
- Not here, Carmine! Not a cop!

528
01:12:08,592 --> 01:12:10,492
What?

529
01:12:10,594 --> 01:12:14,052
You open your fuckin' mouth,
I'll blow your head off!

530
01:13:00,043 --> 01:13:01,943
Freddie. Good to see ya.

531
01:13:04,848 --> 01:13:06,748
Where is he?

532
01:13:06,850 --> 01:13:09,512
He's okay. He's in the back.

533
01:13:13,524 --> 01:13:15,924
Come on, girls. Take a hike, huh?

534
01:13:19,029 --> 01:13:20,929
In this room here.

535
01:13:23,800 --> 01:13:26,860
- I wanna talk to him alone first.
- Come on, huh?

536
01:13:36,046 --> 01:13:38,981
I thought I could help you, Senator.

537
01:13:42,853 --> 01:13:45,117
Hagen?

538
01:13:45,956 --> 01:13:49,016
- Listen, Hagen,
I did not-- - No.

539
01:13:49,126 --> 01:13:51,185
- It's all right.
- I didn't do anything.

540
01:13:51,295 --> 01:13:53,422
It's okay.

541
01:13:53,530 --> 01:13:55,794
You're very lucky.

542
01:13:55,899 --> 01:13:58,367
My brother Fredo operates this place.

543
01:13:58,468 --> 01:14:01,266
He was called before anyone.

544
01:14:01,371 --> 01:14:03,100
Now, if this had
happened someplace else...

545
01:14:03,206 --> 01:14:04,264
we couldn't have helped you.

546
01:14:08,345 --> 01:14:12,782
When I woke up I was on the floor...

547
01:14:12,883 --> 01:14:14,783
and I don't know how it happened.

548
01:14:14,885 --> 01:14:16,785
You can't remember?

549
01:14:20,524 --> 01:14:22,549
I passed out.

550
01:14:28,465 --> 01:14:30,365
I'll fix it.

551
01:14:30,467 --> 01:14:32,435
Okay.

552
01:14:38,609 --> 01:14:40,804
It was just a game.

553
01:14:40,911 --> 01:14:42,310
Jesus.

554
01:14:45,082 --> 01:14:46,982
Oh.

555
01:14:52,422 --> 01:14:54,583
Jesus! Jesus!

556
01:14:59,029 --> 01:15:01,759
Jesus God.

557
01:15:01,865 --> 01:15:03,799
Oh, God.

558
01:15:06,136 --> 01:15:09,833
I don't know and I don't
understand why I can't remember.

559
01:15:09,940 --> 01:15:12,773
You don't have to
remember. Just do as I say.

560
01:15:12,876 --> 01:15:15,470
They're putting a
call in to your office.

561
01:15:15,579 --> 01:15:19,515
Explain that you'll be
there tomorrow afternoon.

562
01:15:19,616 --> 01:15:21,743
You decided to spend the night...

563
01:15:21,852 --> 01:15:25,754
at Michael Corleone's
house in Tahoe as his guest.

564
01:15:26,456 --> 01:15:29,357
I do remember that she was laughing.

565
01:15:31,328 --> 01:15:33,228
We'd done it before...

566
01:15:33,330 --> 01:15:36,663
and I know that I could
not have hurt that girl.

567
01:15:37,801 --> 01:15:39,701
This girl has no family.

568
01:15:39,803 --> 01:15:41,794
Nobody knows that she worked here.

569
01:15:41,905 --> 01:15:44,373
It'll be as though she never existed.

570
01:15:47,077 --> 01:15:49,477
All that's left is our friendship.

571
01:16:05,195 --> 01:16:07,095
- Yes?
- I'm sorry, Mrs. Corleone.

572
01:16:07,197 --> 01:16:11,156
- We're not to let you through.
- I'm just going to the market.

573
01:16:11,268 --> 01:16:13,828
Well, if you'll just give us a list,
we'll pick up anything you want.

574
01:16:13,937 --> 01:16:17,168
- Whose orders are these?
- Mr. Hagen's, ma'am. He's coming.

575
01:16:17,274 --> 01:16:20,402
All right, well, I'm just gonna
have to speak to Mr. Hagen.

576
01:16:25,749 --> 01:16:29,344
I wanted to explain this, but
I had business in Carson City.

577
01:16:29,453 --> 01:16:31,478
Now, this is Michael's
request for your safety.

578
01:16:31,588 --> 01:16:34,182
- We can send out for anything.
- I see.

579
01:16:34,291 --> 01:16:36,259
I'm supposed to stay in my house.

580
01:16:36,359 --> 01:16:38,850
No, within the compound would be fine.

581
01:16:38,962 --> 01:16:41,226
I was going to take the children
to New England next week.

582
01:16:41,331 --> 01:16:44,562
- That's off now.
- Am I a prisoner? ls that it?

583
01:16:44,668 --> 01:16:47,136
- That's not the way we look at it.
- All right, come on, kids.

584
01:16:47,237 --> 01:16:49,137
We're going back to the house.

585
01:16:51,508 --> 01:16:53,408
Joe.

586
01:17:39,222 --> 01:17:40,917
Cuba! Cuba!

587
01:18:22,065 --> 01:18:25,000
Most respected gentlemen...

588
01:18:25,101 --> 01:18:27,262
allow me to welcome you
to the city of Havana.

589
01:18:29,406 --> 01:18:34,400
I want to thank this distinguished
group of American industrialists...

590
01:18:36,446 --> 01:18:38,346
for continuing to work with Cuba...

591
01:18:40,116 --> 01:18:42,311
toward the greatest
period of prosperity...

592
01:18:43,954 --> 01:18:45,854
in her entire history.

593
01:18:47,357 --> 01:18:51,350
Mr. William Shaw, representing
the General Fruit Company;

594
01:18:53,263 --> 01:18:55,128
Misters Corngold and Dant...

595
01:18:55,232 --> 01:18:58,030
of United Telephone
and Telegraph Company;

596
01:19:00,303 --> 01:19:02,567
Mr. Petty, regional vice president...

597
01:19:02,672 --> 01:19:05,072
of the Pan American Mining Corporation;

598
01:19:07,777 --> 01:19:09,972
Mr. Robert Allen of
South American Sugar;,

599
01:19:12,315 --> 01:19:14,442
Mr. Michael Corleone of Nevada...

600
01:19:16,319 --> 01:19:19,618
representing our associates in
tourism and leisure activities;

601
01:19:21,157 --> 01:19:24,058
and my old friend and
associate from Florida...

602
01:19:26,196 --> 01:19:28,357
Mr. Hyman Roth.

603
01:19:28,465 --> 01:19:30,228
I would like to take this opportunity...

604
01:19:30,333 --> 01:19:32,198
to thank United
Telephone and Telegraph...

605
01:19:32,302 --> 01:19:34,202
for their lovely Christmas gift:

606
01:19:38,842 --> 01:19:40,742
a solid gold telephone.

607
01:19:43,480 --> 01:19:46,381
Perhaps you gentlemen would
like to take a look at it.

608
01:19:47,884 --> 01:19:49,613
- Mr. President.
- Yes?

609
01:19:49,719 --> 01:19:52,779
Perhaps you would discuss the
status of rebel activity...

610
01:19:52,889 --> 01:19:55,619
and what this can
mean to our businesses.

611
01:19:55,725 --> 01:19:57,192
- Of course.
- Very lovely.

612
01:19:57,294 --> 01:19:59,762
I want to assure you that
although the rebels...

613
01:19:59,863 --> 01:20:03,060
have mounted an impressive
campaign in Las Villas...

614
01:20:09,306 --> 01:20:11,604
my staff indicates with assurance...

615
01:20:11,708 --> 01:20:16,611
we'll drive them out of the city
of Santa Clara before the new year.

616
01:20:19,215 --> 01:20:21,775
And I want to put you all at ease.

617
01:20:21,885 --> 01:20:25,787
We will tolerate no guerillas
in the casinos or swimming pools.

618
01:20:44,674 --> 01:20:46,574
He say that they are making arrest...

619
01:20:46,676 --> 01:20:49,577
and in a few minutes
he'll let us through.

620
01:20:50,113 --> 01:20:52,172
Johnny.

621
01:21:14,704 --> 01:21:17,832
Well, I hope my age is correct.

622
01:21:17,941 --> 01:21:21,035
I'm always accurate about my age.

623
01:21:21,144 --> 01:21:24,705
Make sure that everybody sees
the cake before we cut it.

624
01:21:28,551 --> 01:21:31,247
I'm very pleased...

625
01:21:31,354 --> 01:21:34,255
you were all able to come
from such distances...

626
01:21:34,357 --> 01:21:35,551
to be with me today.

627
01:21:37,494 --> 01:21:40,190
When a man comes to
this point in his life...

628
01:21:41,731 --> 01:21:45,167
he wants to turn over the
things he's been blessed with--

629
01:21:45,268 --> 01:21:47,259
turn them over
to friends--

630
01:21:47,370 --> 01:21:51,602
as a reward for the friends he's had...

631
01:21:51,708 --> 01:21:56,941
and to make sure that everything
goes well after he's gone.

632
01:21:57,047 --> 01:21:59,709
- Not for years.
- Hear, hear.

633
01:21:59,816 --> 01:22:03,650
The doctors would disagree,
but what do they know?

634
01:22:05,155 --> 01:22:10,183
These are wonderful things
that we've achieved in Havana...

635
01:22:10,293 --> 01:22:13,353
and there's no limit to
where we can go from here.

636
01:22:13,463 --> 01:22:18,230
This kind of government knows how
to help business, to encourage it.

637
01:22:18,334 --> 01:22:22,361
The hotels here are
bigger and swankier...

638
01:22:22,472 --> 01:22:25,100
than any of the rough
joints we've put in in Vegas.

639
01:22:25,208 --> 01:22:28,541
And we can thank our friends
in the Cuban government...

640
01:22:28,645 --> 01:22:31,637
which has put up half of the
cash, with the Teamsters...

641
01:22:31,748 --> 01:22:33,272
on a dollar-for-dollar
basis;

642
01:22:33,383 --> 01:22:36,216
has relaxed restrictions on imports.

643
01:22:36,319 --> 01:22:40,722
What I'm saying is that we have
now what we have always needed:

644
01:22:40,824 --> 01:22:43,588
real partnership with a government.

645
01:22:43,693 --> 01:22:46,287
Smaller piece.

646
01:22:46,396 --> 01:22:48,956
You all know Michael Corleone...

647
01:22:49,065 --> 01:22:51,295
and we all remember his father.

648
01:22:51,401 --> 01:22:55,030
At the time of my retirement or death...

649
01:22:55,138 --> 01:22:59,598
I turn over all my interest
in the Havana operation...

650
01:22:59,709 --> 01:23:00,937
to his control.

651
01:23:01,044 --> 01:23:05,105
But all of you will share.

652
01:23:05,215 --> 01:23:08,912
The Nacionale will go to
the Lakeville Road boys.

653
01:23:09,018 --> 01:23:14,888
The Capri to the Corleone
family. The Sevilla Biltmore also.

654
01:23:14,991 --> 01:23:18,859
But Eddie Levine of Newport will
bring in the Pennino brothers...

655
01:23:18,962 --> 01:23:20,725
Dino and Eddie, for a piece...

656
01:23:20,830 --> 01:23:23,663
and also to handle the
actual casino operations.

657
01:23:23,766 --> 01:23:27,293
And we've saved a piece for
some friends in Nevada...

658
01:23:27,403 --> 01:23:31,066
to make sure that things
go smooth back home.

659
01:23:31,174 --> 01:23:36,134
I want all of you to enjoy your cake...

660
01:23:36,246 --> 01:23:38,146
so enjoy.

661
01:23:38,248 --> 01:23:40,148
- Happy birthday.
- Happy birthday.

662
01:23:41,985 --> 01:23:45,944
I saw an interesting thing happen today.

663
01:23:46,055 --> 01:23:49,183
A rebel was being arrested
by the military police...

664
01:23:49,292 --> 01:23:51,055
and rather than be taken alive...

665
01:23:51,161 --> 01:23:53,789
he exploded a grenade he
had hidden in his jacket.

666
01:23:53,897 --> 01:23:57,298
He killed himself, and he took a
captain of the command with him.

667
01:23:57,400 --> 01:23:59,595
- Right,Johnny?
- Those rebels, they're lunatics.

668
01:23:59,702 --> 01:24:02,967
- Yes, I agree.
- Maybe so.

669
01:24:03,072 --> 01:24:04,664
But it occurred to me...

670
01:24:04,774 --> 01:24:08,107
the soldiers are paid to
fight, the rebels aren't.

671
01:24:08,211 --> 01:24:10,372
What does that tell you?

672
01:24:10,480 --> 01:24:12,380
They could win.

673
01:24:14,217 --> 01:24:17,015
This country has had rebels
for the last 50 years.

674
01:24:17,120 --> 01:24:21,750
It's in their blood. I've been
coming here since the '20s.

675
01:24:21,858 --> 01:24:25,692
We were running molasses out of
Havana when you were a baby...

676
01:24:25,795 --> 01:24:29,390
the trucks owned by your father.

677
01:24:29,499 --> 01:24:31,967
Michael.

678
01:24:38,074 --> 01:24:40,975
I'd rather we talked about
this when we we're alone.

679
01:24:43,913 --> 01:24:46,814
The two million never got to the island.

680
01:24:52,655 --> 01:24:55,783
I wouldn't want it to get around
that you held back the money...

681
01:24:55,892 --> 01:24:59,259
because you had second
thoughts about the rebels.

682
01:25:04,634 --> 01:25:07,569
Ah, sit down, Michael.

683
01:25:07,670 --> 01:25:09,570
Sit down.

684
01:25:16,045 --> 01:25:19,879
If I could only live to see
it, to be there with you.

685
01:25:19,983 --> 01:25:22,315
Ohh.

686
01:25:22,418 --> 01:25:24,886
What I wouldn't give for...

687
01:25:24,988 --> 01:25:26,888
20 more years.

688
01:25:28,458 --> 01:25:30,983
Here we are,
protected--

689
01:25:31,094 --> 01:25:33,153
free to make our profiits
without Kefauver...

690
01:25:33,263 --> 01:25:36,960
the goddamn Justice
Department and the FBl--

691
01:25:37,066 --> 01:25:40,593
90 miles away, partnership
with a friendly government.

692
01:25:42,038 --> 01:25:46,236
Ninety miles. It's nothing.

693
01:25:46,342 --> 01:25:48,902
Just one small step,
looking for a man...

694
01:25:49,012 --> 01:25:52,175
that wants to be President
of the United States...

695
01:25:52,282 --> 01:25:55,649
and having the cash to make it possible.

696
01:25:55,752 --> 01:25:57,652
Michael...

697
01:25:59,255 --> 01:26:02,122
we're bigger than U.S. Steel.

698
01:26:28,284 --> 01:26:30,684
Mikey, how are ya? Okay?

699
01:26:32,722 --> 01:26:35,452
Hiya. Freddie Corleone.

700
01:26:38,661 --> 01:26:40,925
Jesus Christ, what a trip.

701
01:26:41,030 --> 01:26:42,463
The whole time I'm thinkin'...

702
01:26:42,565 --> 01:26:44,658
"What if somebody knows
what I got in here?"

703
01:26:44,767 --> 01:26:49,101
Imagine that. Two million
dollars on the seat next to me.

704
01:26:49,205 --> 01:26:51,105
All right.

705
01:26:52,675 --> 01:26:55,075
- Whoops. Excuse me.
- No, it's okay.

706
01:26:57,380 --> 01:26:59,280
You wanna count it?

707
01:27:03,720 --> 01:27:07,178
Mikey, what the hell's goin' on anyway?

708
01:27:07,290 --> 01:27:09,520
The family's making an
investment in Havana.

709
01:27:09,625 --> 01:27:12,958
- This is a gift for the president.
- Oh.

710
01:27:13,062 --> 01:27:15,030
Well, that's great.

711
01:27:15,131 --> 01:27:17,031
Havana's great.

712
01:27:18,134 --> 01:27:20,034
It's my kind of town.

713
01:27:21,571 --> 01:27:23,664
- Anybody I know in Havana?
- I don't know.

714
01:27:23,773 --> 01:27:25,741
Hyman Roth? Johnny Ola?

715
01:27:29,212 --> 01:27:31,737
No. I never met them.

716
01:27:35,518 --> 01:27:37,816
Listen, Mikey...

717
01:27:37,920 --> 01:27:39,820
I'm kind
of, uh--

718
01:27:43,359 --> 01:27:44,758
kind of nervous from the trip.

719
01:27:44,861 --> 01:27:48,490
Uh, can l-- can I get a,
uh, drink or somethin'?

720
01:27:48,598 --> 01:27:51,863
I thought maybe we'd--
we'd go out together.

721
01:27:51,968 --> 01:27:54,869
I know a place we can spend
some time together. Okay?

722
01:27:57,373 --> 01:28:00,536
Sometimes I think I should've
married a woman like you did...

723
01:28:00,643 --> 01:28:03,043
Like Kay.

724
01:28:03,146 --> 01:28:05,546
Have kids, have a family.

725
01:28:08,217 --> 01:28:11,618
For once in my life be more like...

726
01:28:13,022 --> 01:28:14,614
Pop.

727
01:28:16,859 --> 01:28:21,626
It's not easy to be a
son, Fredo. It's not easy.

728
01:28:21,731 --> 01:28:24,859
Mama used to tease me. She'd
say, "You don't belong to me.

729
01:28:24,967 --> 01:28:28,494
You were left on the
doorstep by gypsies."

730
01:28:28,604 --> 01:28:31,471
Sometimes I think it's true.

731
01:28:31,574 --> 01:28:33,474
You're no gypsy, Fredo.

732
01:28:35,111 --> 01:28:37,102
Mikey,
I--

733
01:28:37,213 --> 01:28:39,113
I was mad at you.

734
01:28:46,355 --> 01:28:50,291
Why didn't we spend
time like this before?

735
01:28:50,393 --> 01:28:52,793
You want a drink, right? Waiter.

736
01:29:00,603 --> 01:29:03,470
- How do you say banana daiquiri?
- Banana daiquiri.

737
01:29:03,573 --> 01:29:05,837
- That's it?
- That's it.

738
01:29:05,942 --> 01:29:08,843
- Uh, uno banana daiquiri.
- Banana daiquiri. Si, senor.

739
01:29:08,945 --> 01:29:11,345
And, uh, a club soda.

740
01:29:19,188 --> 01:29:21,986
Senator Geary's flying in from
Washington tomorrow night...

741
01:29:22,091 --> 01:29:24,491
with some people, some
government people...

742
01:29:24,594 --> 01:29:27,757
and I want you to show
'em a good time in Havana.

743
01:29:30,099 --> 01:29:32,533
It's my specialty, right?

744
01:29:32,635 --> 01:29:35,798
- Can I trust you with something?
- Ofcourse, Mike.

745
01:29:39,575 --> 01:29:42,942
In the evening, we're all invited
to the presidential palace...

746
01:29:43,045 --> 01:29:45,605
a reception to bring in the new year.

747
01:29:45,715 --> 01:29:47,615
After it's over...

748
01:29:47,717 --> 01:29:50,242
they're gonna take me
home in a military car...

749
01:29:50,353 --> 01:29:54,050
alone, for my protection...

750
01:29:54,156 --> 01:29:57,557
and before I reach my
hotel I'll be assassinated.

751
01:30:15,912 --> 01:30:18,972
- Who?
- Roth.

752
