It was Roth who tried
to kill me in my home.

753
01:30:29,492 --> 01:30:31,551
It was Roth all along.

754
01:30:31,661 --> 01:30:36,894
He acts like I'm his
son, his successor...

755
01:30:36,999 --> 01:30:39,934
but he thinks he's gonna live
forever and he wants me out.

756
01:30:45,041 --> 01:30:46,133
How can I help?

757
01:30:46,242 --> 01:30:49,609
You just go along as
though you know nothing.

758
01:30:49,712 --> 01:30:53,648
- I've already made my move.
- What move?

759
01:30:53,749 --> 01:30:56,240
Hyman Roth'll never see the new year.

760
01:31:13,569 --> 01:31:16,163
He says you have to take it easy
and he'll give you a prescription.

761
01:31:16,272 --> 01:31:17,534
He'll be back tomorrow.

762
01:31:17,640 --> 01:31:20,074
I want my own doctor.
Fly him in from Miami.

763
01:31:20,176 --> 01:31:22,371
I don't trust a doctor
can't speak English.

764
01:31:28,751 --> 01:31:30,651
Honey, go down to the casino.

765
01:31:30,753 --> 01:31:34,154
- If you're sure you're better.
- Feel fine.

766
01:31:36,125 --> 01:31:38,889
- Play the bingo game.
- Nice to see you, Mr. Paul.

767
01:31:38,995 --> 01:31:40,963
-Just make yourself at home.
- Thank you.

768
01:31:42,832 --> 01:31:44,231
My sixth sense tells me...

769
01:31:44,333 --> 01:31:46,858
your brother Fredo brought
a bag full of money.

770
01:31:46,969 --> 01:31:50,132
Where is it?

771
01:31:50,239 --> 01:31:52,673
You're pulling out?

772
01:31:52,775 --> 01:31:56,677
Just wanna-- I
just wanna wait.

773
01:32:00,049 --> 01:32:02,643
How do you feel?

774
01:32:02,752 --> 01:32:04,947
Terrible. I'd give four million...

775
01:32:05,054 --> 01:32:08,285
just to be able to take
a piss without it hurting.

776
01:32:08,391 --> 01:32:11,690
Who had Frank Pentangeli killed?

777
01:32:11,794 --> 01:32:14,160
The Rosato brothers.

778
01:32:14,263 --> 01:32:17,824
I know. But who gave the go-ahead?

779
01:32:17,933 --> 01:32:20,834
I know I didn't.

780
01:32:28,044 --> 01:32:30,569
There was this kid I grew up with.

781
01:32:30,680 --> 01:32:32,841
He was younger than me.

782
01:32:32,948 --> 01:32:35,439
Sort of looked up to me, you know.

783
01:32:35,551 --> 01:32:39,112
We did our first work together.

784
01:32:39,221 --> 01:32:41,280
Worked our way out of the street.

785
01:32:41,390 --> 01:32:43,381
Things were good. We
made the most of it.

786
01:32:44,727 --> 01:32:47,218
During Prohibition...

787
01:32:47,329 --> 01:32:49,297
we ran molasses into Canada.

788
01:32:49,398 --> 01:32:51,866
Made a fortune. Your father too.

789
01:32:54,403 --> 01:32:57,429
As much as anyone...

790
01:32:57,540 --> 01:33:00,065
I loved him and trusted him.

791
01:33:03,112 --> 01:33:06,570
Later on he had an idea...

792
01:33:06,682 --> 01:33:08,843
to build a city...

793
01:33:08,951 --> 01:33:12,648
out of a desert stopover for G.I.s
on their way to the West Coast.

794
01:33:14,724 --> 01:33:18,421
That kid's name was Moe Green...

795
01:33:18,527 --> 01:33:21,758
and the city he invented was Las Vegas.

796
01:33:23,499 --> 01:33:25,933
This was a great man...

797
01:33:26,035 --> 01:33:28,526
a man of vision and guts...

798
01:33:28,637 --> 01:33:33,802
and there isn't even a plaque or
a signpost or a statue of him...

799
01:33:33,909 --> 01:33:36,810
in that town.

800
01:33:36,912 --> 01:33:40,370
Someone put a bullet through his eye.

801
01:33:41,751 --> 01:33:44,982
No one knows who gave the order.

802
01:33:45,087 --> 01:33:48,215
When I heard it I wasn't angry.

803
01:33:48,324 --> 01:33:50,349
I knew Moe; I knew he was headstrong.

804
01:33:50,459 --> 01:33:54,361
Talking loud, saying stupid things.

805
01:33:54,463 --> 01:33:57,694
So when he turned up dead...

806
01:33:57,800 --> 01:34:00,997
I let it go...

807
01:34:01,103 --> 01:34:04,334
and I said to myself...

808
01:34:04,440 --> 01:34:08,342
"This is the business we've chosen."

809
01:34:08,444 --> 01:34:11,242
I didn't ask...

810
01:34:11,347 --> 01:34:13,247
who gave the order...

811
01:34:13,349 --> 01:34:16,284
because it had nothing
to do with business.

812
01:34:24,927 --> 01:34:28,829
That two million in
a bag in your room--

813
01:34:31,767 --> 01:34:33,667
I'm going in...

814
01:34:33,769 --> 01:34:35,828
to take a nap.

815
01:34:35,938 --> 01:34:38,031
When I wake...

816
01:34:38,140 --> 01:34:41,803
if the money's on the table
I'll know I have a partner.

817
01:34:41,911 --> 01:34:44,311
If it isn't, I'll know I don't.

818
